A ‘battle of al-Ghuwayr’ ( yawm al-Ghuwayr ) is mentioned (al-Iṣfahānī, Aghānī , xxiv:24) as having taken place between Arab tribes in early Islamic times; al-Ghuwayr (‘the little cave’) is said to be the name of several locations in Arabia (Yāqūt, Muʿjam al-buldān , s.v.). It is not clear why it is mentioned here; perhaps it alludes to an ancient proverb (‘Perhaps ill luck will come from al-Ghuwayr’, see al-Maydānī, Majmaʿ , ii:21).
